            "answer_text": "It wasn\u2019t \u201cjust a case\u201d of anything that involves the word \u201cmight\u201d. Ken Ribet proved that Frey\u2019s curve, defined from a counterexample to FLT, cannot be modular. Frey\u2019s curve is a semistable elliptic curve. Wiles and Taylor proved that all semistable elliptic curves are modular. That\u2019s it. There are no \u201cmight imply\u201d\u2019s anywhere here, no \u201cif\u201ds or \u201cbut\u201ds. The combined efforts of Wiles, Taylor, Ribet, Serre, Frey, Hellegouarch and numerous other mathematicians who contributed to building the edifice on which these proofs rest, provide a complete proof of FLT. ",
