            "answer_text": "Yes it was proven though I cannot attempt to understand the whole proof I\u2019ve read enough about it to understand the monumental achievement it was to prove it. In maths you string together a bunch of statements like: \u201cIf A is true then B cannot be true\u201d or \u201cif A is true then B must be true\u201d. They\u2019re conditional but not an implication. This was how the world around fermats last theorem was until the proof. Enough of these were strung together to logically get from a known proven starting point to the conclusion that it must be true, if only all the conditionals were true. You can read quite a few good (e.g. SIMON SINGH) books on this journey and some of the key pieces that were proven along the way to the complete proof. I will never be able to understand the complete proof, I\u2019m sure there are very few who can but I can understand how the pieces could be put together and from that understand that they have been there it together in a way that proves the theory. Hope this helps. ",
